        "text": "Ahead of the upcoming COP26 summit, climate activists are flooding streets around the world. Have the literati taken environmental justice into account? In *The Intellectual*, we have weighed different answers. Some essays have [https://academic.oup.com/isle/article/26/4/944/5580444 drawn] attention to the conspicuous absence of justice concerns from recent cli-fi, while others [https://muse.jhu.edu/article/739696/summary argued] that the dystopian novel has already moved on to a dispirited ‘post-pessimism’.\n\n\n\n\n"
